---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import '../styles/about.css';

const favorites = [
  {
    label: 'Books',
    items: [
      { title: 'The Grid', by: 'Gretchen Bakke', annot: 'The book that made me want to do this work in the first place.' },
      { title: 'Power Metal', by: 'Vince Beiser', annot: 'Currently reading. Required for anyone working in clean tech.' },
      { title: '[Book three]', by: '[Author]', annot: '[Why it stuck.]' },
    ],
  },
  {
    label: 'People I learn from',
    items: [
      { title: 'Jesse Jenkins', by: 'Princeton ZERO Lab', annot: 'Energy systems modeling done in public.' },
      { title: '[Person]', by: '[Where]', annot: '[For what.]' },
      { title: '[Person]', by: '[Where]', annot: '[For what.]' },
    ],
  },
  {
    label: 'Trails',
    items: [
      { title: '[Trail name]', by: '[Where]', annot: '[Why.]' },
      { title: '[Trail name]', by: '[Where]', annot: '[Why.]' },
    ],
  },
  {
    label: 'Albums for thinking',
    items: [
      { title: '[Album]', by: '[Artist]', annot: '[For what kind of work.]' },
      { title: '[Album]', by: '[Artist]', annot: '[For what kind of work.]' },
    ],
  },
];

const nowItems = [
  { verb: 'Working on', text: '[Current project or focus]', sub: '[One line of context.]' },
  { verb: 'Reading', text: 'Power Metal — Vince Beiser', sub: '[A line on what’s standing out.]' },
  { verb: 'Learning', text: '[A skill, a tool, a topic]', sub: '[Why now.]' },
  { verb: 'Planning', text: '[Trip, talk, event]', sub: '[When.]' },
];
---
<Layout title="About — Parker Tikson" description="A longer answer to so what do you do — how Parker Tikson got into energy systems work, and the things outside it that make it possible.">

  <header class="page">
    <div class="h-grid">
      <div class="h-tag">§ About</div>
      <div>
        <h1>The longer answer to <em>“so what do you do?”</em></h1>
        <p class="h-deck">
          A few paragraphs in plain English about how I got here, what keeps me showing up to the work,
          and the things outside it that make the work possible.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </header>

  <section class="letter">
    <div class="letter-grid">
      <div class="letter-meta">
        <span class="lbl">Written</span>
        <span class="val">November 2026</span>
        <span class="lbl">From</span>
        <span class="val">Berkeley, CA</span>
        <span class="lbl">Reading time</span>
        <span class="val">~3 minutes</span>
      </div>

      <div class="prose">
        <p>
          [Open with something specific and concrete — not "I've always loved the environment."
          Try: a moment, a place, a problem that first made you pay attention. Maybe a summer
          spent somewhere, a class that broke something open, a particular blackout or wildfire
          that made the abstract suddenly real.]
        </p>

        <p>
          [Bridge into your trajectory — what your bachelor's gave you, what work afterward
          taught you, what made you go back for the master's. The shape I'd aim for: not a
          résumé in prose, but the <em>reasoning</em> behind the moves.]
        </p>

        <div class="pull">
          [A pull quote here — one sentence that captures what you actually believe about the
          work. Could be a line from above, could be its own thought.]
        </div>

        <p>
          [What you care about right now. The questions you wake up thinking about. Why
          California's grid in particular, or why energy systems more broadly. Specific is
          better than grand — "I want to understand why DER programs underperform their
          targeting" lands harder than "I want to fight climate change."]
        </p>

        <p>
          [The personal layer. What you do when you're not in front of a model — the
          photography, the trail running, the sourdough, the long drives, whatever it is.
          This is where the page earns its "earnest and personal" register. Two or three
          sentences. Specific details, not categories.]
        </p>

        <p>
          [Optional close — what you're trying to do next, who you'd love to hear from,
          what kind of conversation you're hoping this site starts. Generous, not pleading.]
        </p>

        <div class="signoff">
          With genuine warmth,
          <span class="name">Parker</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="favs">
    <div class="favs-grid">
      <div class="favs-head">
        <h2>Things I keep coming back to</h2>
        <p class="h-meta">A working list, updated when I notice it's gone stale</p>
      </div>

      <div class="favs-cats">
        {favorites.map(cat => (
          <div class="fav-cat">
            <div class="cat-lbl">{cat.label}</div>
            <ul>
              {cat.items.map(item => (
                <li>
                  {item.title}
                  <span class="by">{item.by}</span>
                  <span class="annot">{item.annot}</span>
                </li>
              ))}
            </ul>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="now-band">
    <div class="now-grid">
      <div class="now-head">
        <h2>What I'm doing now</h2>
        <p class="h-meta">Inspired by Derek Sivers' /now page convention</p>
        <div class="updated"><span class="pulse"></span>Updated Nov 2026</div>
      </div>

      <div class="now-list">
        {nowItems.map(item => (
          <div class="now-item">
            <div class="now-verb">{item.verb}</div>
            <div class="now-text">
              {item.text}
              <span class="sub">{item.sub}</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="connect">
    <div class="lbl">§ Get in touch</div>
    <h2>If any of this resonates, <em>I'd love to hear from you</em>.</h2>
    <div class="actions">
      <a class="btn primary" href="mailto:parker_tikson@berkeley.edu">Email me</a>
      <a class="btn" href="#">LinkedIn</a>
      <a class="btn" href="#">GitHub</a>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>
